description.narrative:
The project wants to be a response to low agricultural productivity in Yatenga Province by capacity building, support and advocacy actions to improve access to sources of production for small for small farmers. This project is a process&nbsp;that started since 2012 and for current period, the objectives are:
Global objective: Contributing to economic and equitable social development of people in the Yatenga Province.
&nbsp;
Specific objectives:
1. To imrpove the performance (yield, processing, preservation) 30% of the practice of agriculture, livestock and exploitation of forest resources in the rural communes of Kain, Oula, Koumbri and Barga.
2. To contribute to increase of monetary income&nbsp;of the direct beneficiaries in the implementation of the project areas by 20%.
&nbsp;
At the end of project the mains expected results are:
&nbsp;
Result 1: the Beneficiaries (farmers, producers, transformative) common of Kain, Oula, from Koumbri and Barga in Yatenga province have improved access to inputs / equipment and production facilities, storage and processing thirty.
&nbsp;
Result 2: The beneficiaries (farmers, producers, transformative) common of Kain, Oula, from Koumbri and Barga in the province of Yatenga) know the good practices of production, conservation and transformation and exercise them in their tasks. 
Result 3: Proven technologies and techniques of efficiency developed by research in connection with the activities of the beneficiaries (production, storage and processing) areas of the implementation of the program are disseminated and adopted.
Result 4: The right holders (farmers, producers and transformative) APROS in the intervention area have an added value in marketing their products.
The project will be implemented in the Yatenga region in northern Burkina par l'Association pour la Promotion des Oeuvres Sociales. the target groupe are small farmers, an particular accent will be on the right of women to have their own fields. A law exists but since the application poses a serious problem. The project aims to work with the authorities, men and women of the same time.
